        "title": "[codex] Add generic KubeVirt and external providers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a generic KubeVirt provider that provisions VM leases through `kubectl`, connects through `virtctl`, and supports configurable templates, namespaces, resources, storage, and SSH forwarding\n- add an external executable provider protocol so private control planes can integrate through configuration without entering the open-source core\n- keep provider routing state private per lease while preserving reproducible retry and stop behavior\n- document both providers and add configuration, protocol, lifecycle, routing, and failure-path coverage\n\n## Why\n\nCrabbox needs a Kubernetes-native VM backend without coupling the project to any company-specific infrastructure. The external provider supplies the extension boundary for proprietary provisioning and policy while the KubeVirt provider remains portable across compatible clusters.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `go test -race ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go build -trimpath -o /tmp/crabbox-kubevirt ./cmd/crabbox`\n- autoreview completed with no accepted or actionable findings\n\n## Live infrastructure\n\nThe provider lifecycle is covered with command-level fakes and end-to-end backend tests. A real KubeVirt mutation test was not run because it requires access to a KubeVirt cluster with VM lifecycle RBAC, a compatible template, and SSH connectivity.\n",
